## Project Structure & Component Roles

### 📁 `config/` - Configuration Hub
- **`settings.py`**: Central configuration file
  - Model settings (detection/recognition models, thresholds)
  - Camera settings (index, resolution, FPS)
  - Attendance settings (cooldown, minimum images)
  - GPU settings (memory limits, mixed precision)
  - Preprocessing settings (CLAHE, gamma correction)
  - Tracking settings (IOU threshold, max disappeared)
  - Ensemble settings (voting thresholds, model lists)
- **`database_config.py`**: SQLAlchemy engine and session factory

### 📁 `preprocessing/` - Image Enhancement
- **`clahe.py`**: Contrast Limited Adaptive Histogram Equalization
  - Fixes contrast in dimly lit environments
  - Applied to LAB color space L channel only
- **`exposure.py`**: Gamma correction for over-lit/under-lit frames
  - Automatically balances exposure (mean < 50 triggers correction)
- **`pipeline.py`**: Orchestrates preprocessing filters
  - Ensures AI always sees a "clean" face

### 📁 `detection/` - Face Detection System
- **`async_detector.py`**: Background thread wrapper for detection
  - Non-blocking frame submission via queue
  - Returns latest available detections
- **`tiling.py`**: Multi-scale detection for small faces
  - Slices 1080p frames into overlapping tiles (1080x1080)
  - Maps coordinates back to original frame
  - Applies NMS across tiles (IoU 0.4)
- **`ensemble_detection.py`**: Multi-model detection fusion
  - Combines RetinaFace + MTCNN + YuNet detections
  - NMS across all detections
  - Confidence scoring based on agreement
- **`retinaface_onnx.py`**: GPU-accelerated RetinaFace detector
  - Uses ONNX Runtime with CUDA
  - Faster than TensorFlow backend, less VRAM

### 📁 `models/` - AI Model Management
- **`face_detector.py`**: Multi-backend face detector
  - Supports: RetinaFace (ONNX), MTCNN, OpenCV Haar
  - Face quality assessment (blur, size, pose, lighting)
  - Face extraction with padding and super-resolution integration
- **`face_recognizer.py`**: Ensemble face recognition
  - Supports: ArcFace, Facenet512, VGG-Face
  - Generates embeddings for all active models
  - Ensemble voting with consensus logic (threshold 0.5)
  - Model-specific distance thresholds
- **`embeddings_manager.py`**: Embedding cache and storage
  - Loads from pickle cache (fast startup)
  - Falls back to database if cache missing
  - Stores embeddings by student_id and model_name
  - Structure: `{student_id: {model_name: [vectors]}}`
- **`gpu_manager.py`**: GPU memory and model management
  - Singleton pattern for shared GPU state
  - Memory monitoring via pynvml
  - Auto cache clearing at intervals
  - Mixed precision support (FP16)

### 📁 `recognition/` - Recognition Pipeline
- **`async_recognizer.py`**: Background recognition thread
  - Non-blocking crop submission
  - Quality check → Embedding generation → Matching
  - Returns results via track_id lookup

### 📁 `enhancement/` - Image Enhancement
- **`super_resolution.py`**: Face upscaling for small/blurry faces
  - Uses OpenCV DNN SuperRes (FSRCNN/EDSR)
  - Auto-downloads models if missing
  - Only enhances faces < 64px (configurable)
  - Applied before embedding generation

### 📁 `core/` - Business Logic
- **`tracker.py`**: IOU-based face tracker
  - Maintains unique IDs across frames
  - Tracks: box, disappeared count, embeddings_buffer, identity_stability
  - Max disappeared: 15 frames (configurable)
  - IOU threshold: 0.3 (configurable)
- **`attendance_manager.py`**: Attendance marking logic
  - Track-based evidence accumulation (requires 5 consistent matches)
  - Cooldown system (prevents duplicate marking, default 3600s)
  - Cleans stale tracks automatically
- **`camera_handler.py`**: Threaded camera capture
  - Separate thread for low-latency frame access
  - FPS monitoring
  - Frame preprocessing (horizontal flip)
  - Multi-camera support via source config
- **`unknown_face_handler.py`**: Unknown face logging
  - Saves images with timestamps
  - Logs to database for review
  - Cooldown to prevent flooding

### 📁 `database/` - Data Layer
- **`models.py`**: SQLAlchemy ORM models
  - `Student`: Student information (id, student_id, name, email, enrollment_date)
  - `FaceEmbedding`: Face embeddings (student_id, embedding_vector JSON, model_name)
  - `AttendanceRecord`: Attendance logs (student_id, timestamp, confidence, status)
  - `UnknownFace`: Unrecognized faces (timestamp, image_path, reviewed flag)
- **`crud.py`**: Database operations
  - Student CRUD (add, get, list)
  - Embedding operations (add, get_all_for_recognition)
  - Attendance operations (mark, query history)
  - Unknown face operations (log, get_unreviewed, mark_reviewed)

### 📁 `scripts/` - Utility Scripts
